step.reason:
\begin{align}
  &3\cos x + 2\sin x=t \\
  \implies &\left(-3\sin x +2\cos x\right)dx = dt \\
\end{align} \\
\therefore \int\dfrac{(2\cos x-3\sin x)dx}{2(3\cos x + 2\sin x)}
  =\int \dfrac{1}{2t}dt

